<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;"><br>
<br>
<br>
</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><u><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;text-transform:uppercase;">ExxonMobil Chairman REX W. TILLERSON commented</font></u></b></font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">:</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&#8220;Earnings in the period rose 3 percent from the third quarter of
2013, driven by higher margins and improved operations in the Downstream and
Chemical businesses, partially offset by the impact of lower Upstream realizations.
</font></b></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></b></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">ExxonMobil&#8217;s quarterly results demonstrate the strength of our
integrated business model. Integration across Upstream, Downstream and Chemical
gives us competitive advantages in scale, efficiency, technical and commercial
capabilities, regardless of market fluctuations over the business cycle.</font></b></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></b></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">The Corporation&#8217;s cash flow from operations and asset sales
through the first nine months of 2014 fully covered net investments and
shareholder distributions.</font></b></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><i><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></i></b></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><b><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">We continue to meet our operational and project development
objectives. Upstream production for 2014 remains on track with previous full&#8209;year
estimates of 4&nbsp;million oil&#8209;equivalent barrels per day as the company
adds new production from project startups.&#8221;</font></b></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#160;&nbsp;</font></p>



<font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;">
&nbsp;</font>

  increased $200&nbsp;million or 3&nbsp;percent from the third quarter of 2013.
  </font></p>

  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.2in;text-align:justify;"><b><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;text-transform:uppercase;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.2in;text-align:justify;"><b><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;text-transform:uppercase;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

  production decreased 4.7&nbsp;percent from the third quarter of 2013.
  Excluding the impact of the expiry of the Abu Dhabi onshore concession,
  production decreased 1&nbsp;percent, with liquids up 0.6 percent and gas down
  2.9 percent.</font></p>
  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.2in;text-align:justify;"><b><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;text-transform:uppercase;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

  into a second nonmonetary exchange agreement with LINN Energy, LLC to add
  17,800 net acres in the Permian Basin to its U.S. oil and natural gas
  portfolio, managed by its subsidiary XTO Energy, Inc. This agreement, coupled
  with the first nonmonetary exchange that closed during the quarter, extends
  XTO&#8217;s leasehold position across the entire Permian Basin to more than
  1.5&nbsp;million acres and net oil&#8209;equivalent production to more than
  95,000&nbsp;barrels per day. </font></p>

  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.2in;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;">ExxonMobil announced
  the startup of the Tapis enhanced oil recovery (EOR) project, which is
  Malaysia&#8217;s first large-scale enhanced oil recovery project and will utilize </font><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-GB style="font-size:11.0pt;">the </font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;">immiscible&nbsp;</font><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-GB style="font-size:11.0pt;">
  water-alternating-gas process to increase overall field recovery. </font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;">The project
  exemplifies ExxonMobil's leadership in technology application and global
  project execution to maximize reserves recovery from producing fields.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>

<p align=center style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;mso-border-shadow:yes;mso-padding-alt:31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt;text-align:center;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;"><a name="_GoBack_0"></a><font style="mso-no-proof:yes;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">- 2 -</font></font></font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;">&nbsp;</font></p>

</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_3"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0.4in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0.4in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0.5in; PADDING-LEFT: 0.5in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;mso-pagination:widow-orphan no-line-numbers;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:.7pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><u><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;line-height:115%;">Third Quarter 2014 vs. Third Quarter 2013</font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:8.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;line-height:150%;text-decoration:none;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Upstream
earnings were $6,416&nbsp;million in the third quarter of 2014, down $297&nbsp;million
from the third quarter of 2013. Lower realizations decreased earnings by $670&nbsp;million.
Favorable volume mix effects increased earnings by $340&nbsp;million. All other
items increased earnings by $30&nbsp;million.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">On
an oil&#8209;equivalent basis, production decreased 4.7&nbsp;percent from the
third quarter of 2013. Excluding the impact of the expiry of the Abu Dhabi
onshore concession, production decreased 1&nbsp;percent.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Liquids
production totaled 2,065&nbsp;kbd (thousands of barrels per day), down
134&nbsp;kbd from the third quarter of 2013. The Abu Dhabi onshore concession
expiry reduced volumes by 148&nbsp;kbd. Excluding this impact, liquids
production was up slightly as project ramp&#8209;up and work programs more than
offset field decline, divestment impacts and higher downtime.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Third
quarter natural gas production was 10,595&nbsp;mcfd (millions of cubic feet per
day), down 319&nbsp;mcfd from 2013. Field decline and lower entitlement volumes
were partly offset by new production from Papua New Guinea and work programs.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Earnings
from U.S. Upstream operations were $1,257&nbsp;million, $207&nbsp;million higher
than the third quarter of 2013. Non&#8209;U.S. Upstream earnings were $5,159&nbsp;mi</font><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">llion, down $504&nbsp;million from the prior year.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Downstream
earnings were $1,024&nbsp;million, up $432&nbsp;million from the third quarter
of 2013.&#160; Stronger margins, primarily refining, increased earnings by
$820&nbsp;million. Volume and mix effects increased earnings by
$100&nbsp;million. All other items, primarily foreign exchange impacts,
decreased earnings by $490&nbsp;million. Petroleum product sales of
5,999&nbsp;kbd were 32&nbsp;kbd lower than last year's third quarter. </font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Earnings
from the U.S. Downstream were $460&nbsp;million, up $145&nbsp;million from the third
quarter of 2013. Non&#8209;U.S. Downstream earnings of $564&nbsp;million were $287&nbsp;million
higher than last year.&#160; </font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>


<DIV bclFooter>


<p align=center style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;mso-border-shadow:yes;mso-padding-alt:31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt;text-align:center;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;"><a name="_GoBack_0"></a><font style="mso-no-proof:yes;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">- 3 -</font></font></font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_4"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0.4in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0.4in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0.5in; PADDING-LEFT: 0.5in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;mso-pagination:widow-orphan no-line-numbers;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:.7pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Chemical
earnings of $1,200&nbsp;million were $175&nbsp;million higher than the third
quarter of 2013. Margins increased earnings by $210 million, with improved
commodities realizations partly offset by weaker specialties. Volume and mix
effects increased earnings by $10&nbsp;million. All other items decreased
earnings by $40 million. Third quarter prime product sales of 6,249&nbsp;kt
(thousands of metric tons) were essentially flat with last year's third
quarter.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Corporate
and financing expenses were $570&nbsp;million for the third quarter of 2014, up
$110&nbsp;million from the third quarter of 2013.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">During
the third quarter of 2014, Exxon Mobil Corporation purchased 30&nbsp;million
shares of its common stock for the treasury to reduce the number of shares
outstanding at a cost of $3&nbsp;billion. Share purchases to reduce
shares outstanding are currently anticipated to equal $3&nbsp;billion in the fourth
quarter of 2014. Purchases may be made in both the open market and through
negotiated transactions, and may be increased, decreased, or discontinued at
any time without prior notice. </font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

2013</font></u></b></p>

  percent to $21.03 from full year 2013.</font></p>
  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.2in;text-align:justify;"><b><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;text-transform:uppercase;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

  outstanding.</font></p>
  <p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.2in;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;text-transform:uppercase;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Earnings
of $25,950&nbsp;million increased $1,720&nbsp;million from 2013. Earnings per
share increased 11&nbsp;percent to $6.04.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Upstream
earnings were $22,080&nbsp;million, up $2,025&nbsp;million from the first nine
months of 2013. Lower prices and volumes were more than offset by favorable mix
effects, increasing earnings by a net $470&nbsp;million. All other items,
primarily asset sales, increased earnings by $1.6&nbsp;billion.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">On
an oil&#8209;equivalent basis, production was down 5.3&nbsp;percent compared to
the same period in 2013. Excluding the impact of the expiry of the Abu Dhabi
onshore concession, production decreased 2&nbsp;percent.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Liquids
production of 2,087&nbsp;kbd decreased 105&nbsp;kbd compared to 2013.&#160; The Abu
Dhabi onshore concession expiry reduced volumes by 137&nbsp;kbd. Excluding this
impact, liquids production was up 1.5&nbsp;percent, driven by project ramp&#8209;up
and work programs.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>


<DIV bclFooter>


<p align=center style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;mso-border-shadow:yes;mso-padding-alt:31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt;text-align:center;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;"><a name="_GoBack_0"></a><font style="mso-no-proof:yes;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">- 5 -</font></font></font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_6"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0.4in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0.4in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0.5in; PADDING-LEFT: 0.5in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;mso-pagination:widow-orphan no-line-numbers;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:.7pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Natural gas production of 11,115&nbsp;mcfd decreased
703&nbsp;mcfd from 2013, as expected U.S. field decline and lower European demand
were partially offset by project ramp&#8209;up and work programs.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;text-decoration:none;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Earnings
from U.S. Upstream operations were $3,694&nbsp;million, up $689&nbsp;million
from 2013. Earnings outside the U.S. were $18,386&nbsp;million, up
$1,336&nbsp;million from the prior year.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Downstream
earnings of $2,548&nbsp;million increased $15&nbsp;million from 2013. Lower
margins, mainly refining, decreased earnings by $280&nbsp;million.&#160; Volume and
mix effects increased earnings by $460&nbsp;million. All other items, primarily
unfavorable foreign exchange and tax impacts, partially offset by lower
operating expenses, decreased earnings by $160&nbsp;million. Petroleum product
sales of 5,886&nbsp;kbd increased 35&nbsp;kbd from 2013.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">U.S.
Downstream earnings were $1,619&nbsp;million, up $17&nbsp;million from 2013. Non&#8209;U.S.
Downstream earnings were $929&nbsp;million, a decrease of $2&nbsp;million from
the prior year.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Chemical
earnings of $3,088&nbsp;million increased $170&nbsp;million from 2013. Higher
margins increased earnings by $20&nbsp;million, while volume and mix effects
increased earnings by $140&nbsp;million. All other items increased earnings by
$10&nbsp;million. Prime product sales of 18,516&nbsp;kt were up 530&nbsp;kt from
2013, driven by increased Singapore production. </font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Corporate
and financing expenses were $1,766&nbsp;million in the first nine months of
2014, up $490&nbsp;million from 2013, primarily due to unfavorable tax impacts.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">Gross
share purchases for the first nine months of 2014 were $9.9&nbsp;billion,
reducing shares outstanding by 100&nbsp;million shares.</font></p>





<DIV bclFooter>


<p align=center style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;mso-border-shadow:yes;mso-padding-alt:31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt;text-align:center;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;"><a name="_GoBack_0"></a><font style="mso-no-proof:yes;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">- 6 -</font></font></font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_7"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0.4in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0.4in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0.5in; PADDING-LEFT: 0.5in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;mso-pagination:widow-orphan no-line-numbers;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:.7pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;">Estimates of key financial and operating data follow.&#160; </font></p>

<div style="border:none;border-bottom:double windowtext 1.5pt;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in;">

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;padding:0in;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

</div>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><b><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">ExxonMobil
will discuss financial and operating results and other matters during a webcast
at 8:30&nbsp;a.m. Central time on October 31, 2014.&#160; To listen to the event or access
an archived replay, please visit </font></b><b><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">www.exxonmobil.com</font></i></b><b><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;">.&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<div style="border:none;border-bottom:double windowtext 1.5pt;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in;">

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;padding:0in;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

</div>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><u><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">Cautionary
statement</font></u></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">Statements
relating to future plans, projections, events or conditions are forward&#8209;looking
statements.&#160; Actual results, including project plans, costs, timing, and
capacities; capital and exploration expenditures; resource recoveries; and
share purchase levels, could differ materially due to factors including:
changes in oil or gas prices or other market or economic conditions affecting
the oil and gas industry, including the scope and duration of economic
recessions; the outcome of exploration and development efforts; changes in law
or government regulation, including tax and environmental requirements; the
outcome of commercial negotiations; changes in technical or operating
conditions; and other factors discussed under the heading &quot;Factors
Affecting Future Results&quot; in the &#8220;Investors&#8221; section of our website and in
Item 1A of ExxonMobil's 2013 Form 10-K.&#160; We assume no duty to update these statements
as of any future date.&#160; </font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;text-decoration:none;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>





<DIV bclFooter>


<p align=center style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;mso-border-shadow:yes;mso-padding-alt:31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt 31.0pt;text-align:center;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;"><a name="_GoBack_0"></a><font style="mso-no-proof:yes;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">- 7 -</font></font></font><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;mso-pagination:widow-orphan no-line-numbers;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:.7pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><i><u><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Frequently
used terms</font></u></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:8.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">This
press release includes cash flow from operations and asset sales, which is a
non&#8209;GAAP financial measure.&#160; Because of the regular nature of our asset
management and divestment program, we believe it is useful for investors to
consider proceeds associated with the sales of subsidiaries, property, plant
and equipment, and sales and returns of investments together with cash provided
by operating activities when evaluating cash available for investment in the
business and financing activities.&#160; A reconciliation to net cash provided by
operating activities is shown in Attachment II.&#160; References to quantities of
oil or natural gas may include amounts that we believe will ultimately be
produced, but that are not yet classified as &#8220;proved reserves&#8221; under SEC
definitions.&#160; Further information on ExxonMobil's frequently used financial and
operating measures and other terms is contained under the heading
&quot;Frequently Used Terms&quot; available through the &#8220;Investors&#8221; section of
our website at exxonmobil.com.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:8.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.5in;"><i><u><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">Reference
to Earnings</font></u></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:.5in;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:8.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:4.5pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">References
to corporate earnings mean net income attributable to ExxonMobil (U.S. GAAP)
from the consolidated income statement.&#160; Unless otherwise indicated, references
to earnings, Upstream, Downstream, Chemical and Corporate and Financing segment
earnings, and earnings per share are ExxonMobil's share after excluding amounts
attributable to noncontrolling interests.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:4.5pt;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:4.5pt;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">&nbsp;</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;"><i><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;">The
term &#8220;project&#8221; as used in this release can refer to a variety of different
activities and does not necessarily have the same meaning as in any government
payment transparency reports.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-right:4.5pt;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:150%;">&#160;&nbsp;</font></p>

  <p align=right style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:right;"><font color=black face=Arial,sans-serif style="font-size:9.0pt;">1.1 </font></p>

$0.1G in 3Q14, $0.2G in 2Q14, $0.2G in 1Q14, $0.3G in 4Q13, $0.4G in 3Q13.</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;">The 3Q14 beginning
and ending balances include restricted cash of $0.2G and $0.1G, respectively.</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif style="border:none;"><font face=Arial,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;">PP&amp;E
Adds / Investments and Advances includes PP&amp;E adds of ($8.2G) and net
advances of $0.3G.</font></font></p>
